 labeled training set, and how does it work?"],"metadata":{"id":"EzTCXjdb8bM9"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ans: -\n","\n","The training set is used to train the algorithm, and then you use the trained model on the test set to predict the response variable values that are already known. The final step is to compare the predicted responses against the actual (observed) responses to see how close they are."],"metadata":{"id":"FlYPG-Ll8eon"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"b7luoLcU8gUR"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 4.What are the two most important tasks that are supervised?"],"metadata":{"id":"nlQBrZIw8gtw"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ans: -\n","\n","The two most common supervised tasks are regression and classification. Common unsupervised tasks include clustering, visualization, dimensionality reduction, and association rule learning."],"metadata":{"id":"1OyU78uV8jxr"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"RQrzW-em8lVm"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 5.Can you think of four examples of unsupervised tasks?"],"metadata":{"id":"6kIhxY278lxy"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ans: -\n","\n","Four common unsupervised tasks inclused clustering, visualization, dimensionality reduction , and association rule learning."],"metadata":{"id":"bW5WXaq08pAj"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"metadata":{"id":"_Pc83Uez8qVO"},"execution_count":null,"outputs":[]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## 6.State the machine learning model that would be best to make a robot walk through various unfamiliar terrains?"],"metadata":{"id":"e_fbjQ6o8qwG"}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["Ans: -\n","\n","The best Machine Learning algorithm to allow a robot to walk in unknown terrain is Reinforced Learning, where the robot can learn from response of the terrain to optimize itself."],"metadata":{"id":"nOtt5ORX8vli"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":[],"met